#entry("/img/headshots/agoeva.png", style: "max-width:300px;")[
  = #link("mailto:aleksandrina.goeva@utoronto.ca")[Dr. Aleksandrina Goeva]
  Aleksandrina Goeva is an Assistant Professor at the University of Toronto’s Donnelly Centre, with affiliations in the Departments of Molecular Genetics and Computer Science, a Faculty Affiliate at the Vector Institute for Artificial Intelligence, and a Visiting Scientist at the Broad Institute of MIT and Harvard.
  She received her BSc in Applied Mathematics from Sofia University, and her MSc and PhD from Boston University in Mathematics and Statistics respectively.
  She then completed her postdoctoral training at the Stanley Center for Psychiatric Research at the Broad Institute of MIT and Harvard.

  In addition to her research, Aleksandrina is actively involved in building scientific communities across disciplines.
  She has served as a co-chair and steering committee member of the #link("https://www.broadinstitute.org/mia/about-mia")[MIA] initiative at the Broad Institute, organized international workshops on representation learning in biology at #link("https://neurips.cc/virtual/2022/workshop/49966")[NeurIPS] and #link("https://iclr.cc/virtual/2025/workshop/23999")[ICLR], and is a founding member of the #link("https://hdsr.mitpress.mit.edu/early-career-board")[Early Career Board] at the Harvard Data Science Review.
  She is also deeply committed to teaching and mentorship, with over a decade of experience teaching across multiple institutions.
  Her research program has been supported by #link("https://giving.broadinstitute.org/broadignite/team/aleks-goeva")[competitive] #link("https://nserc-crsng.canada.ca/en/funding-opportunity/discovery-horizons-pilot")[funding], as well as #link("https://temertymedicine.utoronto.ca/news/university-toronto-and-karolinska-institutet-announce-2026-mats-sundin-fellowships-human")[international] and #link("https://www.linkedin.com/posts/aleksandrina-goeva-736754129_excited-to-share-that-arhan-rupani-and-i-activity-7445520160108576770-4Kmi")[institutional] fellowships.
]

